data.name: ttcheckItemsLimited
data.value: Include Pins that have a limited quantity in vanilla (Axion, Dilaton, Dibaryon, and Sfermion).

data.name: ttgrpChanceDifficulty
data.value: Checked Difficulties are included in the randomization.

data.name: ttgrpItemsDifficulty
data.value: Checked Difficulties are included in the randomization.

data.name: ttnumChanceMax
data.value: The maximum drop rate. All randomized drop rates will be lower or equal to this number.

data.name: ttnumChanceMin
data.value: The minimum drop rate. All randomized drop rates will be higher or equal to this number.

data.name: ttnumChanceWeight
data.value: The weights with which to randomize the drop rates for each difficulty.

data.name: ttradioChanceRandomC
data.value: Make the drop rates completely random between the minimum and maximum drop rates.

data.name: ttradioChanceRandomW
data.value: Make the drop rates random but somewhat controlled with weights. This allows for certain difficulties to have lower/higher drop rates. The difficulty with the lowest weight will have drop rates closer to the minimum drop rate while the difficulty with the highest weight will have drop rates closer to the maximum drop rate. The weights scale linearly.

data.name: ttradioItemsRandomA
data.value: Make Noise drop random pins while making all pins available this way. Pig Noise are included. This will always affect all difficulties as this is too restrictive otherwise.

data.name: ttradioItemsRandomC
data.value: Make Noise drop random pins with no other limitations. Pig Noise are included.

data.name: ttradioItemsShuffleC
data.value: Take the full vanilla set of dropped pins, and randomize which Noise drops what. Pig Noise are excluded and keep their drops unchanged. This means that all pins that are obtainable through drops in vanilla are still obtainable in the same way and no new pins are dropped.

data.name: ttradioItemsShuffleS
data.value: Take each Noise's vanilla set of dropped pins, and shuffle which Noise drops which set of pins. Pig Noise are excluded and keep their drops unchanged. The shuffling keeps the corresponding difficulty. For example, a Nefastraven could end up having a Dixiefrog's drops (50 Yen on Easy, 100 Yen on Normal, 500 Yen on Hard and 1 Yen on Ultimate). This means that all pins that are obtainable through drops in vanilla are still obtainable in the same way and no new pins are dropped.

data.name: ttradioItemsUnchanged
data.value: Don't change what pins Noise drop.
